-- Hungary Stocks: Gedeon Richter, OTP Bank Are Active in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-03-28T09:05:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-egis-are-active-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
was little changed at 18,781.52 as of 10:44 a.m. in Budapest.
The following are among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today.  Stock symbols follow company names.  Gedeon Richter Nyrt. (RICHT)  , Hungary’s biggest
drugmaker, rose the most in two weeks after the brokerage unit
of KBC Groep NV increased its fair value estimate for the stock
by 10 percent to 44,051 forint per share, maintaining a buy
recommendation. The shares gained 1.7 percent to 37,745 forint.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, headed
for a second month of declines, on speculation the country will
face further dispute with international lenders on the
conditions of starting bailout negotiations. The shares fell 0.5
percent to 3,875 forint. That brings the stock’s decline this
month to 3.1 percent, following a 0.4 percent drop in February.  To contact the reporter on this story:
